            <td>
                <p style="text-align:center"><img alt="" src="backbone.png" style="width: 450px; height: 350px" /></p></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <p style="text-align:center"><asp:Label ID="lblSentence16" runat="server" Text="The human body is a marvelously complicated work of machinery, consisting of bones, ligaments, discs, and muscles. And just like the machines commonly used in industrial settings, if there&#8217;s a problem with one component, the entire infrastructure could be in trouble.  " Font-Bold="True"></asp:Label></p>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <p style="text-align:center"><img alt="" src="doctor.png" style="width: 450px; height: 350px" /></p></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="height: 22px">
                <p style="text-align:center">
                    <asp:Label ID="lblSentence17" runat="server" Text="Dr. Lawrence is a chiropractor that has witnessed first-hand the unbearable effects of back pain and has built his professional career on the foundation of educating and assisting individuals who want to stay in the best shape possible for as long as possible. He realized the significance that sacroiliac belts can play in helping the affected as they recover from painful episodes and the importance of using them alongside a carefully prescribed plan of rehabilitation. The problem was that most belts were ineffective and poorly constructed. As the years went on and more research began to support the idea of using sacroiliac belts as a way for patients to return to their previous level of function before injury, the belts that were made available to consumers refused to evolve with the times. That&#8217;s why Dr. Lawrence and his team set out to turn the sacroiliac belt market on its head, and little did they know that in doing so, they&#8217;d be starting a revolution!  " Font-Bold="True"></asp:Label></p>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <p style="text-align:center"><img alt="" src="backbeltlogo3.png" style="width: 450px; height: 350px" /></p></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <p style="text-align:center"><asp:Label ID="lblSentence18" runat="server" Text="The Reconstruct Back Belt is an innovation in assistive devices that has long been overdue. Taking the evidence-supported benefits of using a back brace to a new level, this brace improves upon the many flaws that have plagued traditional products. Dr. Lawrence knew that sacroiliac belts provided a well-warranted measure of relief against back pain, but many relied on cheap Velcro and elastic band components. Neither material would allow users to continually adjust the brace throughout the day, and elastic would fatigue over time, losing its ability to provide support for extended periods. " Font-Bold="True"></asp:Label></p>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <p style="text-align:center"><img alt="" src="beltopsia.png" style="width: 600px; height: 180px" /></p></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="height: 22px">
                <p style="text-align:center"><asp:Label ID="lblSentence19" runat="server" Text="The Reconstruct Back Belt is crafted from high-grade materials that are able to withstand regular daily use without losing their ability to function as intended. The belt employs a special BOA reel tension system that allows for easy adjustment any time of the day. Whether you need more or less amounts of support, a simple turn of the wheel located on the side on the brace is all it takes to find your custom sweet spot of comfort. Unlike traditional back belts that wrap around the waist at navel height, the Reconstruct Back Belt sits just a tad lower.  " Font-Bold="True"></asp:Label></p>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
